Regional governor Maksim Kositsky had expressed fear of military bombardment in West Ukraine as Russia withdrew from Kyiv. Kositsky on Telegramsaid that “No casualties were reported following explosions Tuesday in the Lviv region in western Ukraine.”.
Regional Governor Maksim Kositsky on Telegram stated: “Explosions near Radekhiv. “Everybody must remain in shelters.” This was in a town about 70 kilometres (40 miles) northeast of Lviv.
Regional Governor Maksim Kositsky in another post on Telegram later said: “As of this hour, there is no information on victims.”
 
